	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-22T02:36:50">GLI Finance Limited (GLIF) is a Guernsey-based investing company. The Company's objective is to produce a stable and predictable dividend yield, with long term preservation of net asset value. The Company seeks to achieve its objective through the provision of secured lending to small and medium sized companies. The Company invests primarily in senior debt, senior subordinated debt and junior subordinated debt. The maximum investment size, at the time of the investment, will be limited to 15% of the Company's gross assets. It invests in a range of sectors, such as healthcare, private clients, financial services, property, leisure, retail, media, software, publishing and other. GMB Partners LLP (GMB) in United Kingdom, European and US CLO paper and senior secured loans, serves as the Company's investment advisors.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-13T02:53:12">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, GLI Finance Ltd revenues increased 39% to L8.9M. Net income totaled L393K vs. loss of L10.8M. Revenues reflect Realised losses increase of 98% to -L81K, Other income increase of 75% to L2.2M, Gain/ (loss) on foreign currency transac increase from -L232K to L333K. Net Income reflects Loss on disposal of subsidiary decrease from L10.1M (expense) to L0K, Foreign exchange decrease from L1.9M (expense) to L0K.</Text>
